<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=12902#M12902">203</a> of 369
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 2596 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>-------<BR>CLASS: Necromancer (somewhat casual raider, late GoD/pre-anguish OoW gear)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>HP: Fairly important<BR>Mana:&nbsp; more is always good, but not quite as important as HP<BR>Endurance:&nbsp; N/A.. no use at all for casters<BR>AC:&nbsp;While takeing less damage is very important, for silk classes it seems you can't possibly get enough AC (with how things are set up currenty) to matter.. so I don't really bother with this stat.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>HP Regen:&nbsp; Always usefull<BR>Mana Regen:&nbsp; Use to be one of the most usefull stats out there, but with the low cap and the over-abundance of items.. I generaly am 10ish points over cap without even trying.<BR>Endurance Regen:&nbsp; N/A.. no use at all for casters</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Strength:&nbsp; no real use till you run across a str debuff AE.. a few point are handy, but I don't look for it<BR>Stamina:&nbsp; more hp is good.. but I am way, way overcap<BR>Agility: like the AC, thoreticly very important, but doesn't really seem to help<BR>Dexterity:&nbsp; I don't melee or thow stuff, so no use to me<BR>Charisma:&nbsp; Our charms are increadibly easy to break early, even with maxed Charisma, so I don't bother with them or Charisma<BR>Intelligence: For new Necros this is very important, but again, your going to be way, way overcap by the later parts of the game.<BR>Wisdom: N/A.. No use to Int casters</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Cold Resist:&nbsp; Always, handy, but I don't particularly look for it, better gear tends to have better resists<BR>Disease Resist: Always, handy, but I don't particularly look for it, better gear tends to have better resists<BR>Poison Resist: Always, handy, but I don't particularly look for it, better gear tends to have better resists<BR>Magic Resist: I activily look for this one, because most snares and roots are magic based and getting rooted makes it hard to kite<BR>Fire Resist: Always, handy, but I don't particularly look for it, better gear tends to have better resists</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Attack: I don't melee so I don't look for this<BR>Delay:&nbsp; I don't melee so I don't look for this<BR>Damage:&nbsp; I don't melee so I don't look for this<BR>Range:&nbsp; I don't&nbsp;throw stuff&nbsp;so I don't look for this</DIV>
<DIV>Haste:&nbsp; I don't melee so I don't look for this</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Combat Effects:&nbsp; I don't melee so I don't look for this<BR>Shielding: Seems to help alot more then AC, but most caster stuff that I have come across has very low amouts of this.. but I get what I can<BR>Stun Resist: Very, very important.. Necros don't get&nbsp;as many AAs for&nbsp;channeling through stuns as Enchanters or SKs get, so not getting stunned in the first place is very nice.&nbsp;<BR>Strikethrough:&nbsp; I don't melee so I don't look for this<BR>Spell Shield: Pretty handy to have.. I like it, but wouldn't trade other effects for it&nbsp;&nbsp; Generaly if I am getting hit with nukes, I am free to nuke back with my lifetaps.<BR>Avoidance: Very, very nice.. expecialy with the other&nbsp;stuff (AC/Agility/Mitigation AAs) not helping silk classes much on current content.<BR>Accuracy&nbsp; I don't melee so I don't look for this:<BR>DOT Shielding:&nbsp; Pretty hand to have, but like Spell Shielding, I wouldn't trade other effects for it.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Skill Mods: Other then tradeskill ones they seem pretty useless, most that I have had have been two small (3%ish) to make any difference<BR>Click Effects: depends on the timer, most offesive Click effects have 8+ sec cast timers which make them absoulute junk.&nbsp; Not haveing to spend mana on a spell from an expansion or two back isn't worth haveing to spend 2-3x as long to cast it.&nbsp; Most the self buff ones have a short enough cast timer to be usefull, but most of those are melee oriented.</DIV>
<DIV>Proc Effects:&nbsp;&nbsp; I don't melee so I don't look for this<BR>Worn Effects:&nbsp; Depends on the effect.. most caster worn effects are Spell Focus effects...</DIV>
<DIV>Focus Effects:&nbsp; I don't particularly like this change from one Focus for all resist types.. I have to go from 2 (DoT + DD), to atleast&nbsp;3 (Magic, Fire, Poison) if not 5 (Disease, fairly low damage already, and Cold, very few necro spells use cold, but sometimes its all that sticks) items to get the same effect.&nbsp; Not something that will kill me my any means, but it makes selection difficult because you run out of slots to put gear pretty fast.<BR>-------</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I was rather disappointed with most the DoDh augs(though&nbsp;the augs in general were better then the gear, ick)&nbsp;that came from the instanced single group missions.. Most necros, and probably a few enchanters would have prefered some of&nbsp;the melee rewards (Hp, shielding, stun resist, and avoidance) over the caster rewards (Mana, Mana Regen, DoT Shielding, Spell Shielding)... Every mob melees, very few nuke/DoT hard enough to matter.</DIV></DIV></DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>07-09-2006</span> <span class=time_text>06:32 AM</span>
