<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=12904#M12904">205</a> of 369
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 2573 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			I play two characters and raided with both, though the SK has had to
stand aside while raiding for a while so he is further back
progressionwise. Will be going back to playing both actively however,
so including both.<br>

<br>

<br>

CLASS: Cleric<br>

<div>Progression level: CoA &amp; Tacvi<br>
&nbsp;</div>



<div>HP: Without it you die, but it comes as an added bonus on the mana gear.<br>Mana: Besides specific effects, this is what I look at most when choosing gear.<br>Endurance: n/a<br>AC: I get hit some, but I am not supposed to be a tank. Not that important to me.<br>
 </div>



<div>&nbsp;</div>



<div>HP Regen: Not very important.<br>Mana Regen: VERY important.<br>Endurance Regen: n/a<br>
 </div>



<div>&nbsp;</div>



<div>Strength: Not important, comes with the rest of the gear so does not affect my choice of items.<br>Stamina: Important until maxed, comes with the rest of the gear so does not affect my choice of items.<br>Agility: Not important, comes with the rest of the gear so does not affect my choice of items.<br>
Dexterity: Not important, comes with the rest of the gear so does not affect my choice of items.<br>
Charisma: Not important, comes with the rest of the gear so does not affect my choice of items.<br>
Intelligence: Useless.<br>Wisdom: Important until maxed, comes with the rest of the gear so does not affect my choice of items.<br>
 </div>



<div>&nbsp;</div>



<div>Cold Resist: All resists count equal unless I am lacking in one in particular. Usually does not affect my choice of items.<br>Disease Resist:  All resists count equal unless I am lacking in one in particular. Usually does not affect my choice of items.<br>Poison Resist:  All resists count equal unless I am lacking in one in particular. Usually does not affect my choice of items.<br>Magic Resist:  All resists count equal unless I am lacking in one in particular. Usually does not affect my choice of items.<br>Fire Resist: All resists count equal unless I am lacking in one in particular. Usually does not affect my choice of items. </div>



<div>&nbsp;</div>



<div>Attack: Useless.<br>Delay: Not important.<br>Damage: Not important.<br>Range: n/a<br>
 </div>



<div>Haste: Not important, the only time I melee is usually because I
am a) bored, b) using bash to interrupt a caster or c) to proc the
minor group heal (usually related to a)<br>
 </div>



<div>&nbsp;</div>



<div>Combat Effects: Useless.<br>Shielding: Good to have, but I don't really look for it.<br>Stun Resist: VERY important.<br>Strikethrough: Useless.<br>Spell Shield: Important.<br>Avoidance: VERY important, if I'm going to be attacked I don't want to get hit at all if possible.<br>Accuracy: Useless.<br>DOT Shielding: Good to have, but I don't really look for it.<br>
</div>



<div>&nbsp;</div>



Skill Mods: They don't really do enough to make a difference to me as is.<br>

Click Effects: EXTREMELY important. Above all my clicky mana regen
items and increase mana pool item are very dear to me. I love them and
they love me, know what I mean? I knew you did. In general, I love
clickies and I want more of them.<br>


Proc Effects: Not important, but the group heal proc on the Time cleric hammer is at least vaguely useful.<br>

Worn Effects: I always did like Faerune, even though you could buy see
invis and enduring breath through AAs nowadays I'd rather not have to
spend my AAs (of which I still have too few, almost at 400 now though)
on that. <br>

Focus Effects: EXTREMELY important. Mana preservation and improved
healing above all, but spell haste (well, beneficial such at least),
extended range and extended enhancement are also very important.<br>

<br>

-------<br>

<br>

CLASS: Shadow Knight<br>


<div>Progression level: Time/Qvic<br>
&nbsp;</div>



<div>HP: Without it you die. Comes with the ac gear though, but it is my fourth stat.<br>Mana: Comes with the other gear, not really important.<br>Endurance: Since we don't have much to spend it on, it is not something I really need more of.<br>AC: EXTREMELY important. The more AC, the better. I won't sacrifice ALL hps and such for pure AC, but this is my primary stat.<br>
</div>



<div>&nbsp;</div>



<div>HP Regen: Good to have, not something I look for.<br>Mana Regen: Important, usually doesn't factor in much in gear choice though.<br>Endurance Regen: Since we don't have much to spend it on, the current regen seems fine.<br>
</div>



<div>&nbsp;</div>



<div>Strength: Important until maxed (for attack), comes with the rest of the gear so does not affect my choice of items.<br>Stamina: Important until maxed (for hp), comes with the rest of the gear so does not affect my choice of items.<br>Agility: Not important (ac gain too low), comes with the rest of the gear so does not affect my choice of items.<br>Dexterity: Important until maxed (for procs), comes with the rest of the gear so does not affect my choice of items.<br>Charisma: Not important (except for DI), comes with the rest of the gear so does not affect my choice of items.<br>Intelligence: Not important, comes with the rest of the gear so does not affect my choice of items.<br>Wisdom: Useless.<br>
 </div>



<div>&nbsp;</div>



<div>Cold Resist: All resists count equal unless I am lacking in one in particular. Usually does not affect my choice of items.<br>Disease Resist: All resists count equal unless I am lacking in one in particular. Usually does not affect my choice of items.<br>Poison Resist: All resists count equal unless I am lacking in one in particular. Usually does not affect my choice of items.<br>Magic Resist: All resists count equal unless I am lacking in one in particular. Usually does not affect my choice of items.<br>Fire Resist: All resists count equal unless I am lacking in one in particular. Usually does not affect my choice of items. </div>



<div>&nbsp;</div>



<div>Attack: Good to have, not something that makes or breaks gear choice though.<br>Delay:
The lower the better (well, depending on whether it's 1h or 2h there is
a limit). I look more at ratio than actual delay however.<br>Damage: The more the better. I look more at ratio than actual damage however.<br>Range: I don't use a bow.<br>
 </div>



<div>Haste: Very important to have of course. But I don't consider dps to be my main purpose, except when soloing.<br>
 </div>



<div>&nbsp;</div>



<div>Combat Effects: I don't see nearly enough of this around. Would like more but hard to find.<br>Shielding: Extremely important. Third stat I look for.<br>Stun Resist: Very very important. Fifth stat I look for.<br>Strikethrough: Good to have, don't base gear choices on it however.<br>Spell Shield: Good to have, don't base gear choices on it however.<br>Avoidance: Extremely important. Second stat I look for.<br>Accuracy: Good to have, don't base gear choices on it however.<br>DOT Shielding: Good to have, don't base gear choices on it however.<br>
 </div>



<div>&nbsp;</div>



Skill Mods: They don't really do enough to make a difference to me as is.<br>


Click Effects: I love clickies! AC clicky above all of course, but clickies are good in general. More!<br>


Proc Effects: Yes please. Runes and lifetaps preferred, the rest is not that interesting.<br>


Worn Effects: Faerune is nice. Damage shield isn't bad.<br>

Focus Effects: Good to have. Mana preservation, spell damage (magic for
lifetaps and disease for the rest) and extended range at least.<div></div>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
