<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=12909#M12909">210</a> of 369
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 2489 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>CLASS: BEASTLORD
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>HP:&nbsp; High - Beastlords dont have a reliable way to reduce their agro and build it fairly quickly (especially those with Rake) since our pets add to our agro (stun DD).&nbsp; I usually sit 3rd or 4th on the agro list which means if things go down hill im going to be getting agro quicker.<BR>Mana:&nbsp; High - Alot of our DPS relies on us being able to summon our DoDh 68 swarm pet and use our ice DD's.&nbsp; The DoDh pet is expensive to keep up and running and we lose a decent amount of DPS when we cant use it.<BR>Endurance:&nbsp;Becoming alot more important with the recent additions of the Empathic disc (3000&nbsp;end to activate) and Rake&nbsp;<BR>AC: Medium - Were leather...naturally we wont be getting much in the way of AC.&nbsp; I find it fairly important since I find myself tanking for groups alot and since we mitigate for crap (even with defensive AA's)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>HP Regen: Medium - Not all too concerned about HP regen being Iksar and having about 10 hp regen.&nbsp; I dont have much downtime when soloing.<BR>Mana Regen: High - Again a good majority of our DPS relies on us being able to summon the DoDh pet and nuke.&nbsp; Cant do that without mana.<BR>Endurance Regen:&nbsp;DESPERATLY NEEDED VERY HIGH - Endurance Regen has become alot more important for us in the past two expansions.&nbsp; DoDh added the Empathic Fury disc which takes a whopping 3k endurance just to use.&nbsp; PoR added the Rake ability which uses 180 endurance at a refresh rate of 30 secs.&nbsp; This isnt too bad but if you've been rezzed recently&nbsp;and havent had time to sit down for a good 10 mins to regen your endurance then you're screwed.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Strength: Low - Negated at higher leves where stats are maxxed<BR>Stamina: Med - Negated at higher leves where stats are maxxed<BR>Agility: High - Negated at higher leves where stats are maxxed<BR>Dexterity: High - Negated at higher leves where stats are maxxed<BR>Charisma: Low - Negated at higher leves where stats are maxxed<BR>Intelligence: Low - Negated at higher leves where stats are maxxed<BR>Wisdom: High - Negated at higher leves where stats are maxxed</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Cold Resist: Med - Negated at higher leves where stats are maxxed<BR>Disease Resist: Med - Negated at higher leves where stats are maxxed<BR>Poison Resist: Med - Negated at higher leves where stats are maxxed</DIV>
<DIV>Magic Resist: Med - Negated at higher leves where stats are maxxed<BR>Fire Resist: Med - Negated at higher leves where stats are maxxed</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Attack: Very Important - We dont get double attack via a normal skill like other melee do.&nbsp; Our DPS relies heavily on us being able to hit as often as we can for as much as we can.<BR>Delay:&nbsp;Depends - Depends very much on the weapon.<BR>Damage:&nbsp;Depends - Depends very much on the weapon.<BR>Range: Depends - Depends very much on the weapon.</DIV>
<DIV>Haste: Important - Every melee needs a haste item to be more efficient.&nbsp; There isnt really a shortage of them out there.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Combat Effects: Important - DD's are nice so are lifetaps.&nbsp; I would kill for a combat effect that restores some of your mana (beastlord).<BR>Shielding: Important - Since I spend alot of time tanking and eatting rage shielding is very important.<BR>Stun Resist: Medium - Not as much important...I dont get stunned too much.<BR>Strikethrough: Very Important - We dont get double attack via a normal skill like other melee do.&nbsp; Our DPS relies heavily on us being able to hit as often as we can for as much as we can.<BR>Spell Shield: Important - We're melee...we spend most our time near the mob doing DPS and as such were not really able to pull out of range of the AE's and still be an effective DPSer<BR>Avoidance: Important - Who wants to get hit on?<BR>Accuracy: VERY IMPORTANT - for the same reason as Strikethrough and Attack.&nbsp; Beastlords dont get to hit as often as other melee so we need to make each hit count<BR>DOT Shielding: Important - Same reason as Spell Shielding.&nbsp; We cant really avoid most AE's so we need to be able to shave damage off of them.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Skill Mods: BEGGING - Please for the love of God give us a Rake skill mod.<BR>Click Effects: Important - AE Debuffers suck...clickies for the win.<BR>Proc Effects: Important - Procs rock...selling my body for a mana steal proc<BR>Worn Effects: Important - Mana pres, regens, pretty much anything that helps our DD's or improves our Pets.<BR>Focus Effects: Same as worn.<BR></DIV></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1298641">Ikkorus</a><br><a href="http://www.pakcafan.com">Pak`Cafan</a>
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
