		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>CLASS:&nbsp; Enchanter, end-game raider
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>HP:&nbsp; Very Important, I have to stand toe-to-toe with mobs on almost a daily basis and usually take some hits before I can&nbsp; get my job done.&nbsp; I die from lack of hp, not lack of mana.&nbsp; If I'm dead, I can't do any of my jobs.<BR>Mana:&nbsp; Important, can't do much without mana<BR>Endurance:&nbsp; Meh, I don't use this<BR>AC: Minimal Importance, As a silk class, my soft cap is so low I'm probably well over it.&nbsp; The only spot&nbsp; really look at for a high AC item is my shield.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>HP Regen:&nbsp;&nbsp; Minimal<BR>Mana Regen:&nbsp; Minimal - Its very easy to max this out<BR>Endurance Regen: Don't use</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Strength: Not Important<BR>Stamina: Not Important<BR>Agility: Not Important<BR>Dexterity: Not Important<BR>Charisma:&nbsp; Important since charming relies on charisma<BR>Intelligence: Important at lower levels<BR>Wisdom: Not used</DIV>
<DIV>Stats in general are very easy to max out at higher levels, I don't even look at the basic stats when I decided to upgrade a piece of gear or not.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Cold Resist: Semi-Important<BR>Disease Resist: Semi-Important<BR>Poison Resist: Semi-Important<BR>Magic Resist: Easy for an enchanter to raise with our own spells<BR>Fire Resist: Semi-Important</DIV>
<DIV>I place some value in resists in general and wish gear were better balanced with them.&nbsp; CoA gear was horrible at doing this, Demi isn't much better.&nbsp; At one point my fire resist was almost 100 points below my other resists.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Attack: Not Important<BR>Delay: Not Important<BR>Damage: Not Important<BR>Range: Not Important</DIV>
<DIV>Haste: Not Important</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Combat Effects: Not Important<BR>Shielding: Semi-Important<BR>Stun Resist: Important<BR>Strikethrough: Not Important<BR>Spell Shield: Very Important<BR>Avoidance: Very Important - but easy to max<BR>Accuracy: Not Important<BR>DOT Shielding: Very Important</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Skill Mods: Like them, but not too important<BR>Click Effects: Love them, give us more<BR>Proc Effects: Not Important, but fun<BR>Worn Effects: Meh<BR>Focus Effects: Very Important - My gear choices are driven by focus effects and making sure I have the important ones covered.&nbsp; It can get fristrating having to hang on to a dated piece of gear just to keep the focus on it, or when a focus you need/want to upgrade is only available in one slot.&nbsp; Equally frustrating is seeing a key piece of gear (silk pants in Demi) with a focus effect that is absolutely useless for 3 of the 4 silk classes.<BR></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
