		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>CLASS: WEEEZARD 
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>HP: Very important - a dead wizard is no dps<BR>Mana:&nbsp;Important for shortish fights as it&nbsp;limits our full burn time<BR>Endurance: not important<BR>AC: not that important</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>HP Regen: not that important<BR>Mana Regen: Most important along with clickies, in most situations our damage is mana regen limited, we are a damage class with nothing meaningful to suplement our mana based spell damage.<BR>Endurance Regen: not important</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Strength: not important<BR>Stamina: important as it affects hp<BR>Agility: not important<BR>Dexterity: not important, does nothing for a wizard (melee skillups?)<BR>Charisma: not important, Unfailing divinity 3 &gt; CHA<BR>Intelligence: important as it affects mana pool<BR>Wisdom: not important</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Cold Resist: moderately important<BR>Disease Resist: moderately important<BR>Poison Resist: moderately important<BR>Magic Resist: more important than other resists as more detrimental spells / AEs are MR checked than the others<BR>Fire Resist: moderately important</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Attack: not important<BR>Delay: not important<BR>Damage: not important<BR>Range: not important</DIV>
<DIV>Haste: not important</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Combat Effects: not important<BR>Shielding: slightly important<BR>Stun Resist: quite important<BR>Strikethrough: not important<BR>Spell Shield: important<BR>Avoidance: quite important<BR>Accuracy: not important<BR>DOT Shielding: quite important</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Skill Mods: does +spec evocation do anything these days?&nbsp; My Maelin's robe had no effect on the amount of mana consumed by DD spells when I got it.<BR>Click Effects: Most important along with mana regen, Maelin's pants - need I say more.&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Proc Effects: not important<BR>Worn Effects: not important&nbsp;&nbsp; Ferocity III for a wizard? <BR>Focus Effects: very important and I'm annoyed as a very annoyed person that is particularly annoyed that day that all my focus effects will stop working with the increase in levels that is coming.&nbsp; New content gives higher focus % (what are we up to, +60% to DDs now?) that <STRONG>also</STRONG> works to higher levels.&nbsp; Please stop with the need to replace focus effects every time new levels are introduced, those at the bleeding edge will get their higher % effects from new content first, there is no need for the rest of us to see our effects rendered useless at the same time.&nbsp; My warrior's "Blade of War" from PoP will still proc Enraging Blow for 700 hate no matter what level he or the NPC's he fights reach, my wizard's Noqfiel's wand of infinite enimity (that cost me a stupendous amount of DKP as it was the first 45% fire focus in guild and I think the 2nd or third on AB at the time ) will do almost nothing when she gets to level 75 and casts a level 75 fire based DD.&nbsp; There is a huge melee to caster imbalance in this which I believe needs to be addressed.<BR>Pointiness of&nbsp;Hats : Very important! <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-very-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>edit: my point in progression is hard to specify.&nbsp; From my gear you can see I was in an endgame guild until OOW came out and the level increase made me quit within a couple of months as I didn't have time outside raiding to make the levels and RL made it difficult for me to attend raids at that time as well.&nbsp; Now I'm raid leading an alliance of small "family" type&nbsp;guilds into Time (hence the concern about level 67 capped focus effects).</DIV><p>Message Edited by onomatopoeia on <span class=date_text>07-10-2006</span> <span class=time_text>04:09 PM</span>
