			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<P><FONT face=Verdana size=2>CLASS: Beastlord<BR><BR>HP:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Very High. My HP puddle gets smaller and smaller relative to mob's damage..<BR>Mana:&nbsp;&nbsp; Moderate. My mana pool needs to be big enough to be able to buff my group and have something left. Regen is more important.<BR>Endurance:&nbsp;&nbsp; Moderate. Again regen is the key not the absolute number<BR>AC:&nbsp;&nbsp; Very High. Anything that keeps me from getting hit with the full amount all the time. It may do little over the cap but that doesn't stop me from scratching thogether all I can.<BR><BR>HP Regen: High - I take what I can get but mobs now have damage output that makes HP regen a sideshow - still anything that reduces downtime is good.<BR>Mana Regen: Very High - Mana is DPS, mana helps licking my wounds, mana makes mobs manageable. Much more important than mana pool because it is the difference between downtime and playing.<BR>Endurance Regen: Very VERY High. This is just plain broken at the moment.<BR><BR>Strength: High - Up to the point where it is capped (Only "high" because of class buffs)<BR>Stamina: High - Up to the point where it is capped (Only "high" because of class buffs)<BR>Agility: Very High - Up to the point where it is capped ("very high" because no class buffs available)<BR>Dexterity: Very High - Up to the point where it is capped (Very high even though we gat buffs for Dex. Somehow it seems AWOL on current gear)<BR>Charisma: Low - Important only up to the point where best merchant prices are offered with apprehensive faction.<BR>Intelligence: Very low - Using WIS for casting makes INT seem pointless<BR>Wisdom: Very High - Up to the point where it is capped<BR><BR>Cold Resist: Med - I am no where near the cap so very very important. The type/value of resists on a particular item has influenced the decision whether or not to go for an it on more occasions than any other stat. WTB balance pst! <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0><BR>Disease Resist: Med - see above<BR>Poison Resist: Med - see above<BR>Magic Resist: Med - see above<BR>Fire Resist: Med - see above<BR><BR>Attack: Very Important - Malee damage is more mportant than spell and pet damage. Any raw attack I can get I take.<BR>Delay: I would love to have more choice here especially main hand weapons.<BR>Damage: As long as it fits the delay, i.e. damage output of the weapon is ok.<BR>Range: Not important. Not something I consider very important seeing where my skill is capped.<BR>Haste: Very important - Again it determines my melee damage.<BR><BR>Combat Effects:&nbsp; Very important since the best beastlord weapons are usually weapons whose damage output is to a good part in procs.<BR>Shielding:&nbsp; Very important. Again anything that lowers how much damage I take.<BR>Stun Resist: Any I can get but if I really, really wanted it I should have rolled an ogre.<BR>Strikethrough: Important. Increases my melee damage.<BR>Spell Shield: Depends on how reists will work in the future.<BR>Avoidance: Very Important - We live by the RNG and die by the whims of the RNG.<BR>Accuracy: Important. Increases my melee damage.<BR>DOT Shielding: Depends on how reists will work in the future.<BR><BR>Skill Mods: I have so many other bases top cover that I am not really looking at these.<BR>Click Effects: Please keep them for fun stuff. Not something more to chase.<BR>Proc Effects: Very Important - This is what I look for most when getting a weapon. Especially life taps.<BR>Worn Effects: Anything other than damage shields or fire focus.<BR>Focus Effects: I already dread the day we find out we have to replace all of them again.</FONT></P>	
		</td></tr>
