			<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Merloc-DEV wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>Thanks for all the great feedback so far...</P>
<P>Monks and Bards, sorry for leaving our weight and instrument modifiers, but I was trying to keep the form to as few stats as possible... and I was pretty sure you would remind me. <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></P>
<P>So far I've only skimmed over most of the posts, I'm going to give this thread another week or so for people to post their ideas, then I'll start making profiles for each class based on my own ideas and knowledge of the game.&nbsp; I'll be using the feedback in this thread to make sure I don't miss anything important... any suggestions for future improvements, and opposing points of view will be included as well.</P>
<P>Once I'm done, I'll be using these profiles as a reference point for future item creation... Of course, they won't be set in stone, so if anything new comes up, I can easily add that into the mix.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>Merloc</P><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>Does this mean we're going to see generic pieces of gear for that particular archtype (either armor type or character type) or more class-specific drops/quests?	
